<p><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/spacer.gif width=5><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/headers/current_affairs.gif><center><table width=100%><tr><td background=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/horizon_line.gif><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/spacer.gif height=16></td></tr></table><p><table Border=0 Bgcolor=#181818 Width=100%>
<tr><td colspan=2 Bgcolor=#000000 Align=center><font color=white size=+2>re: Clerics and AA abilities</font>
</td></tr><tr><td width=10% Bgcolor=#101010 Align=center Valign=top><table width=200><tr><td align=center><font size=-1><table><tr><td align=center><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_top.jpg><br clear=all><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_left.jpg><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/portraits/RENALINI.jpg width="104" height="184"><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_right.jpg><br clear=all><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_bottom.jpg></td></tr></table>Legendary  RENALINI RAGESLAYER<br>Level 65 Cleric<br><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_7.gif" title="Star of Achievement"><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_11.gif" title="Silver Order of Leadership"><br>Knight<br><a style="text-decoration:none;" href="main.cgi?fetch=RENALINI"><font size=-1 color="#DDDDDD">RENALINI</font></a><font size=-1>'S LINEAGE</font><br><img src='http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/bio.gif' border=0></font></td></tr></table></td><td width=90% Valign=top><a href=main.cgi?followup=18&forum=9><p align=right><font color=#cccccc>Reply | </a><a href=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/guild-builder/call/main.cgi?action=messages&forum=9><font color=#cccccc>Return</a></p><br clear=all><p><i>Because of the need for CCH rotations on higher tier raid encounters, some of which we are starting to take aim at(Veksar dragon, SSra, Akheva), I think it is important for all our clerics to aim for a base set of AA abilities that will help us maintain the chains longer and more efficiently. With the mod rod nerf endless mana is no longer possible, and regen and mana preservation are king, along with the DPS to end the fight ASAP.<br><br><b>Specialization</b><br><br>Firstly, all clerics should be spec'd alteration(200). I don't know of many who aren't, but there are a few that spec'd evocation running around.<br><br>Spec alteration will save you between 10 and 11% mana per cast, on any spell that uses alteration(healing). This will also effect CH, even though mana preserving focus items do not. I realize that the game descriptions say that every time you cast a spell, you have a chance of making the spec check to save mana, but from all the information I've seen, the mana savings apply to each and every spell cast. Much testing has been done on this, some of which is <A HREF="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm28.showMessage?topicID=23.topic" target="_new">here</A>.<br><br><b>General AA Abilities</b> - must spend 6 points to start Archetype AA.<br><br>Run Speed 3(3 points 1/1/1). Get it. Period. Run3 will help you get around on your own faster, and it will work inside and in dungeons, where SoW and other run speed enchancers will not.<br><br>Where you spend your next 3 points is up to you, however, most of the general abilities are fairly worthless unless you have a ton of AA's and are just trying to find a place to spend them. I would suggest either Metabolism 3(3 points, 1/1/1) or Regeneration 3(3 points, 1/1/1). Metabolism will reduce your food consumption, which will help you conserve stat food if you use it, or keep you from running through stacks of food so fast when using your horse or lizzy, since they eat from your inventory. Regeneration 3 is pretty simple, it raises your regen by 3 hitpoints per tick at level 3.<br><br><b>Archetype AA Abilities</b> - must spend 12 points for Class AA.<br><br>Spell Casting Mastery 3(aka SCM3, 12 points, 2/4/6). Get this. And get it as soon as you can. One of the few things that will save mana on Complete Healing. Again, the in game description says it simply increases your chance for a spec check. This again is not how it really works. Much testing has shown that SCM3 is simply an additional 10% mana savings on every spell cast. With this ability, you now save 11%(spec alter) plus another 10% on every healing spell you cast, including complete healing. At this point, your CH will now cost you somewhere around 320 mana per cast instead of the base 400. At level one, SCM saves you 2%, at level 2 - 5%, and at level 3 - 10%. Although MC1 is only 2 AA points, I would get this first because it saves you more mana than MC1 will regen in a given time frame.<br><br>Mental Clarity(2/4/6). If anything, only get the first level of Mental Clarity. For 2 A points, you get FT I, which isn't too bad. However, 4 points for the second level and 6 points for the third... those points could be better spent elsewhere for now. If you get toa point where you have AA to spend, then come back and get this. First level is good though, 2 AA points will take you just a few hours in PoV or PoS.<br><br>Healing Adept(2/4/6). This increases you healing on direct heals by 2/5/10%. Increases mana efficiency but not really useful for CCH rotations.<br><br>Healing Gift(2/4/6). This gives yo a chance to crit heals. Cute, but not really useful. Really the only reason to get HG3 is beacuse some of the class AA's require it.<br><br>Spell Casting Reinforcement(2/4/6) Again, not terribly useful in this context, although lengthening your HoTs and buffs is nice. Other abilities should come first, however.<br><br><b>Class AA Abilities</b><br><br>Mass Group Buff(9 points) - Yeah, we all know what this is. Get it after you get SCM3 and MC1. Sometimes we wipe after using up Mediic's MGB. Having another cleric or two able to MGB Virtue or Aegolism will be helpful. In some encounters, having a cleric MGB a group heal over time spell during the fight could be useful.<br><br><br>Of couse there are plenty of other useful AA's, many guides have been written on them, I wanted to cover only the abilites that directly affect our healing capability or getting a raid started quickly.<br><br>See <A HREF="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/forums/showthread.php?s=&threadid=15469" target="_new">this thread</A> at EQ Cleric. Towards the bottom, there are a couple of recommended orders for getting AA abilities.<br clear=all><br><font size=-2>(Edited by RENALINI on 8/29/2003 at 10:45a.m.)</font><br></i><br></td></tr><tr><td>
